4-0 scoreline at Man City harsh on Swans - Brendan Rodgers
Media playback is not supported on this deviceSwansea boss Brendan Rodgers says the 4-0 scoreline was "harsh" after watching his side get ripped apart in the second-half of their Premier League debut at Manchester City.Rodgers insist his players can be proud of their efforts and says that his team's Premier League fate will we decided on their home form, not in away matches at Champions League and title-chasing sides.The Swans face Wigan and Sunderland at the Liberty Stadium in their next two Premier League matches.